MILWAUKEE (AP) _ Douglas Dynamics Inc. (PLOW) on Monday reported profit of $8.8 million in its fourth quarter.On a per-share basis, the Milwaukee-based company said it had profit of 38 cents. Earnings, adjusted for one-time gains and costs, were 42 cents per share.The snowplow maker posted revenue of $152.9 million in the period.For the year, the company reported profit of $30.7 million, or $1.29 per share. Revenue was reported as $541.5 million.Douglas Dynamics expects full-year earnings in the range of $1.25 to $2.15 per share, with revenue in the range of $570 million to $630 million._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on PLOW at https://www.zacks.com/ap/PLOW